import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['budgetYear'], bins=31, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['budgetYear'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['budgetYear'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.xlabel('budgetYear')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of budgetYear?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['forecastYear'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['forecastYear'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['forecastYear'].median()))
    plt.xlabel('forecastYear')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of forecastYear?')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8,6))
    ax.boxplot(data['abs_diff'], vert=False, showmeans=True, meanline=True, 
               patch_artist=True, boxprops=dict(facecolor='lightblue', color='black'), 
               meanprops=dict(color='red', linewidth=2), medianprops=dict(color='black', linewidth=2))
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of abs_diff?')
    ax.set_xlabel('abs_diff')
    ax.set_yticklabels(['abs_diff'])
    ax.axvline(data['abs_diff'].median(), color='black', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['abs_diff'].median()))
    ax.axvline(data['abs_diff'].min(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Min: {:.2f}'.format(data['abs_diff'].min()))
    ax.axvline(data['abs_diff'].max(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Max: {:.2f}'.format(data['abs_diff'].max()))
    ax.legend(loc='best')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
